@node "registration" "Registration"

  Registration

  Anyone who is using this program for a  period  of  30  days  or  longer
  should register. When you register you will receive fully working version
  without boring requesters and with all features. By registering you allow
  further development of this or other good software.


  Please send $10 or DM 15 to the following address:

            D.N.A.
            Husova 55
            Ivanovice
            68323
            Czechia

  Do  not  send  cheques.  Only  cash  is  accepted.  Cash  in  registered  letter
  (unregistered works fine too) or international money order are best ways to send
  registration fee.

  Please allow 2-4 weeks for delivery (depending on the continent  you
  live on).

  Look for new updates in internet. It is more eident that new updates will not be
  spread freely and regularly. Only registered users will be informed.

@endnode

@node "limitations" "Limitations"

  Limitations of unregistered version

  Unregisterd versions are limited in their use as  they  lack  certain  features.
  Nevertheless they give you excellent source of information to check out what you
  should register for. They  are  ully  functional.  Also  very  boring  and  time
  absorbing requesters appear very often. Registered version is fast and complete.
  It is available upon registration.

  In unregistered version kicking of kickstarts 3.0 and up is disabled.   :-)

@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

  Kick can be run both from CLI and workbench. When  run  from  workbench,  window
  pops up. When run from CLI default kickstart (selected and saved previously from
  window gadgets) will be kicked if no command line parameter  is  specified.  You
  can specify name of kickstartfile or ROM on command line.

@endnode

@node "windescription" "Window description"

   Window description

   On left there is a list gadget showing all available kickstarts.
   On right there is KICK gadget and SAVE gadget.
   At the right bottom is number of currently running OS.
   At the leftt bottom is name of selected kickstart  which  should  be  booted  on
   startup

@endnode

