@node "listgadget_a" "List gadget"

  List gadget

  List gadget shows all available kickstarts in selected directory.  If  you  want
  any  other description than version to be shown enter text in filecomment gadget
  from workbench.

@endnode

@node "kick_a" "Kick menu or gadget"

 Kick menu or gadget

 Will try to rekick selected kickstart.

@endnode

@node "startup_a" "STARTUP gadget"

  STARTUP gadget

  Sets kickstarts which should be kicked at boottime.

@endnode

@node "about_a" "About item"

  About item

  Information about program.

@endnode

@node "save_a" "Save item"

  Sets kickstarts which should be kicked at boottime.

@endnode

@node "quit_a" "Quit item"

  Quits Kick. You should not use this very often :-)

@endnode

@node "selectdir_a" "Select directory"

 Changes kickstart directory.

@endnode

@node "running_a" "Currently running"

 Sets list gadget on kickstart currently running.

@endnode

@node "getstartupdir_a" "Get startup directory"

 Select directory of kickstartfile kicked on boottime.

@endnode

@node "getlastdir_a" "Get last directory"

 Select last used directory.

@endnode

@node "getlastkickdir_a" "Get last kick directory"

 Select last directory from which kickstart was kicked.

@endnode

@node "kicklist_a" "Kicklist"

  When  selected  Kick  tries  to  read  contents  of  selected  dirrectory   from
  bufferfile.  This  speeds up program since checking all kistarts in directory is
  very time consuming matter (especially when  512k  kickstarts  are  XPK-packed).
  When no such bufferfile in directory is present new bufferfile will be created.

@endnode

@node "refreshkicklist_a" "Refresh kicklist"

  Will refresh all kickstarts in bufferfile (kicklist). Do this when you  put  new
  kickstarts in directory or delete old ones.

@endnode

@node "stools" "Special tools"

  Special tools
@{b}
  CKick
@{ub}
  CKick is CLI kicker written in assebly for speed. It is only cca 900 bytes  big!
  Supports  kickstart  saved  with  with STARTUP gadget or Save menu. You can also
  specify name of kickstratfile on commandline (or  ROM  when  rekicking  back  to
  original  ROM image). Put it in your startup sequence or use directly (ONLY FROM
  CLI).

@{b}
  KickPic
@{ub}
  KickPic is BootPic-like utility which shows nic epicture on  startup  time  when
  only  black screen is available. In this picture is information about current OS
  version, processor, memory... Put it in youur startup sequence.

@{b}
  GetKick
@{ub}
  GetKick is ROM grabber. Copies ROM image to file.

@endnode

